name: Fiat est violentiam - Knife - #1
description: "The term fiat derives from the Latin fiat ("let it be done") used in the sense of an order, decree or resolution." - (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fiat_money) Fiat money keeps our economies violently attached to central governments that can print more money as desired, effectively making their citizens instantly poorer by decree. Most of the modern wars have been financed with fiat money. Most of the weapons and bullets are bought with fiat. HSBC loves laundering the fiat money of the Mexican and Colombian drug cartels and when they are caught, they pay their fines with the same fiat money. Yes, fiat is violence. Let's get free!
